cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper focuses on developing a mobile application for patients to capture medical monitor data and send it to their doctor. This involves designing an interface that is user-friendly and easy to use, which falls under the purview of HCI.
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper presents a robust engine that can recognize digits from medical monitors with high accuracy. This involves using computer vision techniques such as image processing and pattern recognition, which are core topics in CV.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper utilizes machine learning techniques to recognize digits from medical monitors. This involves training a model to recognize patterns in the data, which falls under the purview of ML.
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper involves retrieving and analyzing medical data from patients, which falls under the purview of IR.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper involves developing a mobile application that captures and processes multimedia data (i.e., medical monitor readings), which falls under the purview of MM.
